<subSubSection id="84C66515B62CFFBDFF5482E9FABCD0B4" lastPageId="5" lastPageNumber="221" pageId="3" pageNumber="219" type="description">
<paragraph id="CC63369EB62CFFBBFF5482E9FE31D60D" blockId="3.[151,1437,1109,2036]" pageId="3" pageNumber="219">
<emphasis id="FEA8EA8CB62CFFBBFF5482E9FEDED5FD" bold="true" box="[199,345,1433,1459]" pageId="3" pageNumber="219">Description.</emphasis>
Measurements (in mm) and ratios (range, n = 17): AL: 1.32-1.38, 1.36; HL: 0.55-0.62, 0.58; HW: 0.46-0.54, 0.50; PL: 0.63-0.71, 0.67; PW: 0.44-0.50, 0.47; EL: 0.30-0.36, 0.33; EW: 0.50-0.57, 0.54; AW: 0.54- 0.62, 0.57; ML: 1.02-1.09, 1.05 (n=6); FL: 3.6-3.8, 3.7; TL: 4.1-4.5, 4.3; HL/HW: 1.15-1.20, 1.17; PW/HW: 0.93- 0.96, 0.95; PW/PL: 0.70-0.71, 0.70; EL/PL: 0.48-0.51, 0.49; EW/PW: 1.13-1.14, 1.14; EL/EW: 0.60-0.63, 0.62; AW/EW: 1.08-1.09, 1.09.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="CC63369EB62CFFBBFF54813DFBC5D6C5" blockId="3.[151,1437,1109,2036]" pageId="3" pageNumber="219">
Habitus as in 
<figureCitation id="54E72A1BB62CFFBBFEF1813DFE55D629" box="[354,466,1613,1639]" captionStart="FIGURES 12–22" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1921,1945]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,313,1893]" captionTargetId="figure-60@4.[151,1436,309,1898]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 12–22. Lathrobium amasiacum sp. n. 12—habitus; 13—forebody; 14—head in lateral view; 15—male sternite VII; 16—male sternite VIII; 17— female tergite VIII; 18— female sternite VIII; 19, 20— aedeagus in lateral view; 21, 22— aedeagus in ventral view. Scale bars: 1.0 mm (Figs. 12−13); 0.2 mm (Figs. 14−22)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6405108" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6405108/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="219">Figure 12</figureCitation>
. Body 
<quantity id="0B249B7BB62CFFBBFDB1813DFD2BD626" box="[546,684,1613,1640]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.3" metricValueMax="4.5" metricValueMin="4.1" pageId="3" pageNumber="219" unit="mm" value="4.3" valueMax="4.5" valueMin="4.1">4.1−4.5 mm</quantity>
long. Colouration: whole body uniformly rufous, posterior margin of abdominal segments III–VI distinctly blackish; antennae and legs reddish brown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="CC63369EB62CFFBBFF5481E6FD2FD7E5" blockId="3.[151,1437,1109,2036]" pageId="3" pageNumber="219">
In general appearance similar to 
<taxonomicName id="0BDC4D1DB62CFFBBFDAD81E6FD40D6E1" authorityName="Anlaş" authorityYear="2022" box="[574,711,1685,1711]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Lathrobium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="219" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tokatense">
<emphasis id="FEA8EA8CB62CFFBBFDAD81E6FD40D6E1" box="[574,711,1685,1711]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="219">L. tokatense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but it can be distinguished as follows: colouration of posterior margin of abdominal segments III–VI darker than in 
<taxonomicName id="0BDC4D1DB62CFFBBFC9281CAFC0BD69D" authorityName="Anlaş" authorityYear="2022" box="[769,908,1721,1747]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Lathrobium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="219" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tokatense">
<emphasis id="FEA8EA8CB62CFFBBFC9281CAFC0BD69D" box="[769,908,1721,1747]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="219">L. tokatense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; head approximately 1.15–1.20 times as long as wide (
<figureCitation id="54E72A1BB62CFFBBFE9381ADFE0DD6B9" box="[256,394,1757,1783]" captionStart="FIGURES 12–22" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1921,1945]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,313,1893]" captionTargetId="figure-60@4.[151,1436,309,1898]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 12–22. Lathrobium amasiacum sp. n. 12—habitus; 13—forebody; 14—head in lateral view; 15—male sternite VII; 16—male sternite VIII; 17— female tergite VIII; 18— female sternite VIII; 19, 20— aedeagus in lateral view; 21, 22— aedeagus in ventral view. Scale bars: 1.0 mm (Figs. 12−13); 0.2 mm (Figs. 14−22)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6405108" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6405108/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="219">Figs. 12−13</figureCitation>
and see ratios HL/HW), punctation slightly denser and much more distinct than that in 
<taxonomicName id="0BDC4D1DB62CFFBBFA1581AEFE86D755" authorityName="Anlaş" authorityYear="2022" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Lathrobium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="219" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tokatense">
<emphasis id="FEA8EA8CB62CFFBBFA1581AEFE86D755" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="219">L. tokatense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, antennae 
<quantity id="0B249B7BB62CFFBBFEE58071FD9DD752" box="[374,538,1793,1820]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.35" metricValueMax="1.38" metricValueMin="1.32" pageId="3" pageNumber="219" unit="mm" value="1.35" valueMax="1.38" valueMin="1.32">1.32−1.38 mm</quantity>
long; eyes strongly reduced, with indistinct cornea lenses, but with pigmentation, slightly larger than those in 
<taxonomicName id="0BDC4D1DB62CFFBBFE408056FDDCD771" authorityName="Anlaş" authorityYear="2022" box="[467,603,1829,1855]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Lathrobium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="219" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tokatense">
<emphasis id="FEA8EA8CB62CFFBBFE408056FDDCD771" box="[467,603,1829,1855]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="219">L. tokatense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation id="54E72A1BB62CFFBBFDF88055FD38D771" box="[619,703,1829,1855]" captionStart="FIGURES 12–22" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1921,1945]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,313,1893]" captionTargetId="figure-60@4.[151,1436,309,1898]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 12–22. Lathrobium amasiacum sp. n. 12—habitus; 13—forebody; 14—head in lateral view; 15—male sternite VII; 16—male sternite VIII; 17— female tergite VIII; 18— female sternite VIII; 19, 20— aedeagus in lateral view; 21, 22— aedeagus in ventral view. Scale bars: 1.0 mm (Figs. 12−13); 0.2 mm (Figs. 14−22)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6405108" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6405108/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="219">Fig. 14</figureCitation>
); pronotum longer than wide, approximately 1.4 times as long as wide, punctation much more distinct than that of 
<taxonomicName id="0BDC4D1DB62CFFBBFD54803AFCD7D72D" authorityName="Anlaş" authorityYear="2022" box="[711,848,1865,1891]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Lathrobium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="219" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tokatense">
<emphasis id="FEA8EA8CB62CFFBBFD54803AFCD7D72D" box="[711,848,1865,1891]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="219">L. tokatense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation id="54E72A1BB62CFFBBFCF38039FC6FD72D" box="[864,1000,1865,1891]" captionStart="FIGURES 12–22" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1921,1945]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,313,1893]" captionTargetId="figure-60@4.[151,1436,309,1898]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 12–22. Lathrobium amasiacum sp. n. 12—habitus; 13—forebody; 14—head in lateral view; 15—male sternite VII; 16—male sternite VIII; 17— female tergite VIII; 18— female sternite VIII; 19, 20— aedeagus in lateral view; 21, 22— aedeagus in ventral view. Scale bars: 1.0 mm (Figs. 12−13); 0.2 mm (Figs. 14−22)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6405108" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6405108/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="219">Figs. 12−13</figureCitation>
and see ratios PW/PL); elytra broader than pronotum (
<figureCitation id="54E72A1BB62CFFBBFEDA801DFE48D7C9" box="[329,463,1901,1927]" captionStart="FIGURES 12–22" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1921,1945]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,313,1893]" captionTargetId="figure-60@4.[151,1436,309,1898]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 12–22. Lathrobium amasiacum sp. n. 12—habitus; 13—forebody; 14—head in lateral view; 15—male sternite VII; 16—male sternite VIII; 17— female tergite VIII; 18— female sternite VIII; 19, 20— aedeagus in lateral view; 21, 22— aedeagus in ventral view. Scale bars: 1.0 mm (Figs. 12−13); 0.2 mm (Figs. 14−22)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6405108" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6405108/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="219">Figs. 12−13</figureCitation>
and see ratios EW/PW); abdomen slightly wider than elytra approximately 1.1 times as wide as elytra (
<figureCitation id="54E72A1BB62CFFBBFED180E1FE15D7E5" box="[322,402,1937,1963]" captionStart="FIGURES 12–22" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1921,1945]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,313,1893]" captionTargetId="figure-60@4.[151,1436,309,1898]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 12–22. Lathrobium amasiacum sp. n. 12—habitus; 13—forebody; 14—head in lateral view; 15—male sternite VII; 16—male sternite VIII; 17— female tergite VIII; 18— female sternite VIII; 19, 20— aedeagus in lateral view; 21, 22— aedeagus in ventral view. Scale bars: 1.0 mm (Figs. 12−13); 0.2 mm (Figs. 14−22)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6405108" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6405108/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="219">Fig. 12</figureCitation>
and see ratios AW/EW).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="CC63369EB62CFFBCFF5480C5FE4ED09B" blockId="3.[151,1437,1109,2036]" lastBlockId="4.[151,1436,151,285]" lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="220" pageId="3" pageNumber="219">
Male: sternite VII with a conspicuous clusters of dense dark setae and slightly concave middle of the posterior margin (
<figureCitation id="54E72A1BB62CFFBBFF6480A9FECCD7BA" box="[247,331,2009,2036]" captionStart="FIGURES 12–22" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1921,1945]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,313,1893]" captionTargetId="figure-60@4.[151,1436,309,1898]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 12–22. Lathrobium amasiacum sp. n. 12—habitus; 13—forebody; 14—head in lateral view; 15—male sternite VII; 16—male sternite VIII; 17— female tergite VIII; 18— female sternite VIII; 19, 20— aedeagus in lateral view; 21, 22— aedeagus in ventral view. Scale bars: 1.0 mm (Figs. 12−13); 0.2 mm (Figs. 14−22)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6405108" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6405108/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="219">Fig. 15</figureCitation>
), posterior incision of sternite VIII distinctly asymmetrical, less than 1/3 as long as length of the sternite; pubescence unmodified (
<figureCitation id="54E72A1BB62BFFBCFD8787E7FDEFD0FC" box="[532,616,151,178]" captionStart="FIGURES 12–22" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1921,1945]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,313,1893]" captionTargetId="figure-60@4.[151,1436,309,1898]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 12–22. Lathrobium amasiacum sp. n. 12—habitus; 13—forebody; 14—head in lateral view; 15—male sternite VII; 16—male sternite VIII; 17— female tergite VIII; 18— female sternite VIII; 19, 20— aedeagus in lateral view; 21, 22— aedeagus in ventral view. Scale bars: 1.0 mm (Figs. 12−13); 0.2 mm (Figs. 14−22)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6405108" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6405108/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="220">Fig. 16</figureCitation>
). Aedeagus large, almost symmetrical, with a protrusion bent apically in ventral view (
<figureCitation id="54E72A1BB62BFFBCFEA187CBFE3AD09B" box="[306,445,187,213]" captionStart="FIGURES 12–22" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1921,1945]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,313,1893]" captionTargetId="figure-60@4.[151,1436,309,1898]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 12–22. Lathrobium amasiacum sp. n. 12—habitus; 13—forebody; 14—head in lateral view; 15—male sternite VII; 16—male sternite VIII; 17— female tergite VIII; 18— female sternite VIII; 19, 20— aedeagus in lateral view; 21, 22— aedeagus in ventral view. Scale bars: 1.0 mm (Figs. 12−13); 0.2 mm (Figs. 14−22)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6405108" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6405108/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="220">Figs. 19−22</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="CC63369EB62BFFBCFF5487AFFC63D153" blockId="4.[151,1436,151,285]" pageId="4" pageNumber="220">
Female: posterior margin of tergite VIII weakly angled in middle, pubescence unmodified (
<figureCitation id="54E72A1BB62BFFBCFB4D87AFFAB5D0B7" box="[1246,1330,223,249]" captionStart="FIGURES 12–22" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1921,1945]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,313,1893]" captionTargetId="figure-60@4.[151,1436,309,1898]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 12–22. Lathrobium amasiacum sp. n. 12—habitus; 13—forebody; 14—head in lateral view; 15—male sternite VII; 16—male sternite VIII; 17— female tergite VIII; 18— female sternite VIII; 19, 20— aedeagus in lateral view; 21, 22— aedeagus in ventral view. Scale bars: 1.0 mm (Figs. 12−13); 0.2 mm (Figs. 14−22)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6405108" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6405108/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="220">Fig. 17</figureCitation>
), sternite VIII oblong, its posterior margin convex, pubescence unmodified (
<figureCitation id="54E72A1BB62BFFBCFC108673FC50D153" box="[899,983,259,285]" captionStart="FIGURES 12–22" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1921,1945]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,313,1893]" captionTargetId="figure-60@4.[151,1436,309,1898]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 12–22. Lathrobium amasiacum sp. n. 12—habitus; 13—forebody; 14—head in lateral view; 15—male sternite VII; 16—male sternite VIII; 17— female tergite VIII; 18— female sternite VIII; 19, 20— aedeagus in lateral view; 21, 22— aedeagus in ventral view. Scale bars: 1.0 mm (Figs. 12−13); 0.2 mm (Figs. 14−22)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6405108" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6405108/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="220">Fig. 18</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<caption id="98A36616B62BFFBCFF0480F1FCF8D7AC" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6405108" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6405108" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6405108/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="220" startId="4.[151,264,1921,1945]" targetBox="[151,1436,313,1893]" targetPageId="4">
<paragraph id="CC63369EB62BFFBCFF0480F1FCF8D7AC" blockId="4.[151,1436,1921,2018]" pageId="4" pageNumber="220">
<emphasis id="FEA8EA8CB62BFFBCFF0480F1FED3D7D7" bold="true" box="[151,340,1921,1945]" pageId="4" pageNumber="220">FIGURES 12–22.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="0BDC4D1DB62BFFBCFEC980F1FDCDD7D7" authority="Anlaş, 2022" authorityName="Anlaş" authorityYear="2022" box="[346,586,1921,1945]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Lathrobium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="220" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="amasiacum" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis id="FEA8EA8CB62BFFBCFEC980F1FDCDD7D7" box="[346,586,1921,1945]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="220">Lathrobium amasiacum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="E59B57F7B62BFFBCFDC380F2FD00D7D7" box="[592,647,1922,1945]" pageId="4" pageNumber="220" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
12—habitus; 13—forebody; 14—head in lateral view; 15—male sternite VII; 16—male sternite VIII; 17— female tergite VIII; 18— female sternite VIII; 19, 20— aedeagus in lateral view; 21, 22— aedeagus in ventral view. Scale bars: 1.0 mm (Figs. 12−13); 0.2 mm (Figs. 14−22).
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="CC63369EB62AFFBDFF5487E6FABCD0B4" blockId="5.[151,1437,150,429]" pageId="5" pageNumber="221">
<emphasis id="FEA8EA8CB62AFFBDFF5487E6FE34D0FF" bold="true" box="[199,435,150,177]" pageId="5" pageNumber="221">Comparative notes.</emphasis>
This new species can be distinguished from the geographically closest congeners, i.e., other species with similarly reduced eyes and without cornea lenses, by different shapes of the male and female primary and secondary sexual characters (see key to the microphthalmous 
<taxonomicName id="0BDC4D1DB62AFFBDFC4987AFFB32D0B7" box="[986,1205,223,249]" pageId="5" pageNumber="221">
<emphasis id="FEA8EA8CB62AFFBDFC4987AFFBDAD0B7" box="[986,1117,223,249]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="221">Lathrobium</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
of 
<collectingCountry id="B4CB760EB62AFFBDFB4987AFFAA8D0B4" box="[1242,1327,223,250]" name="Turkey" pageId="5" pageNumber="221">Turkey</collectingCountry>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="84C66515B62AFFBDFF548673FCD6D153" box="[199,849,259,285]" pageId="5" pageNumber="221" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="CC63369EB62AFFBDFF548673FCD6D153" blockId="5.[151,1437,150,429]" box="[199,849,259,285]" pageId="5" pageNumber="221">
<emphasis id="FEA8EA8CB62AFFBDFF548673FEC9D153" bold="true" box="[199,334,259,285]" pageId="5" pageNumber="221">Etymology.</emphasis>
The name refers to 
<collectingRegion id="0E18F87CB62AFFBDFDBE8673FD0BD153" box="[557,652,259,285]" country="Turkey" name="Amasya" pageId="5" pageNumber="221">Amasya</collectingRegion>
, the 
<typeStatus id="1367883CB62AFFBDFD538673FD77D153" box="[704,752,259,285]" pageId="5" pageNumber="221">type</typeStatus>
locality.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="84C66515B62AFFBDFF548656FF33D1E3" pageId="5" pageNumber="221" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="CC63369EB62AFFBDFF548656FF33D1E3" blockId="5.[151,1437,150,429]" pageId="5" pageNumber="221">
<emphasis id="FEA8EA8CB62AFFBDFF548656FD90D10E" bold="true" box="[199,535,294,321]" pageId="5" pageNumber="221">Distribution and bionomics.</emphasis>
This species was collected at six localities in Borabay lake environs in 
<collectingRegion id="0E18F87CB62AFFBDFAD38657FF7ED12B" country="Turkey" name="Amasya" pageId="5" pageNumber="221">Amasya province</collectingRegion>
of the central northern 
<collectingCountry id="B4CB760EB62AFFBDFD95863BFDEDD12B" box="[518,618,331,357]" name="Turkey" pageId="5" pageNumber="221">Anatolia</collectingCountry>
. The 
<typeStatus id="1367883CB62AFFBDFD3A863BFD5ED12B" box="[681,729,331,357]" pageId="5" pageNumber="221">type</typeStatus>
specimens were collected in various kinds of forest by sifting litter at altitudes of 1015 and 
<quantity id="0B249B7BB62AFFBDFE75861FFDBDD1C7" box="[486,570,367,393]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.1" pageId="5" pageNumber="221" unit="m" value="1100.0">1100 m</quantity>
and some specimens were found in MSS traps at altitudes of 1100 and 
<quantity id="0B249B7BB62AFFBDFAF6861FFF37D1E3" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.16" pageId="5" pageNumber="221" unit="m" value="1160.0">1160 m</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
</treatment>
